# Failure Conditions

Reject the Creative Brief if:

The designer must guess.

The copywriter must interpret.

The prompt engineer lacks information.

The production team needs clarification.

The testing objective is unclear.

The KPI is undefined.

The hypothesis is missing.

The creative format is not specified.

Continue refining until every section is production-ready.

---

# Success Criteria

A successful Creative Brief allows any production team to create high-quality assets without asking additional questions.

Everything required for execution is documented.

Nothing important is left to interpretation.

Production can begin immediately after approval.
